	A long shot, perhaps, Chai   ...    but
How does air bleed into the fuel tank as fuel drains out?  If that 
air bleed is blocked, fuel will after a while fail to keep flowing 
...
Crude test of this hypothesis is to leave the fuel filler cap loose 
so that air can enter there.


